  "doc_id": "53474",
  "text": "The detail sub-bands reflect the edges and texture of input images, and the fusion result of detail sub-bands has a decisive influence on the contrast and visibility of details. Mertens et al. [CITATION_1] used the same weight map to fuse all detail sub-bands of a Laplacian pyramid. When the decomposition level is small, the contrast of the fused image is low. At the same time, a loss of detail can be expected to occur near strong edges if the decomposition level is too large.",
  "correct_citation": {
